description.narrative: UNICEF continued providing technical and financial support to improve the skills of nutrition service providers to improve children and adolescent feeding practice and make health facilities baby friendly. UNICEF also supported awareness creation workshops to Women Development Agents, and religious leaders to tackle cultural and religious barriers to proper IYCF practices. These contributed to maintaining high level of breastfeeding until the age of 24 months at 75% in the country . UNICEF is supporting FMOH in the development of a national IYCF-in emergencies guideline which sheds light on key IYCF recommendations during different emergencies including COVID-19. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:24/08/2020
